<p>I read through all the answers but I was looking for a single command to do this. Here is what I did. Added a git alias to .gitconfig</p>

<pre><code>[alias]
      fp = "!f(){ git fetch ${1} ${2} &amp;&amp; git reset --hard ${1}/${2};};f"
</code></pre>

<p>Run your command as </p>

<pre><code>git fp origin master
</code></pre>

<p>equivalent to</p>

<pre><code>git fetch origin master
git reset --hard origin/master
</code></pre>
